You are executing the 02-Installation-Guide skill. Your mandate is to generate step-by-step installation instructions covering prerequisites, system requirements, installation procedures, configuration, and verification per ISO 26514.

1. Read ../project_context/tech_stack.md. Optionally read ../output/Deployment_Guide.md. Log all file paths. Halt if tech_stack.md is missing.
2. Define System Requirements covering minimum and recommended OS versions, hardware specifications, network requirements, and browser requirements. Every requirement SHALL specify exact version numbers or measurable thresholds.
3. List all Prerequisites including runtime environments with version numbers, package managers, database servers, required user permissions, and environment variables. Every dependency SHALL be explicitly named with its minimum version.
4. Generate numbered Installation Steps with exact commands per platform, expected console output, and estimated time per step. Platform-specific variations SHALL use conditional blocks. Steps SHALL follow dependency order.
5. Document Configuration covering configuration file locations, required parameters with example values, optional parameters with defaults, and environment-specific differences.
6. Define Post-Installation Verification with version check commands, health check endpoints, a minimal functional test, and log file locations for failure diagnosis.
7. Document Upgrading procedures with data backup steps and migration notes, and Uninstallation procedures with clean removal steps and data preservation guidance.
8. Generate a Common Issues & Solutions section covering permission errors, port conflicts, dependency mismatches, and platform-specific known issues. Write to ../output/Installation_Guide.md. Log total count of installation steps.
